text: Tshiamiso Sekowe is a South African DJ and music producer professionally known as Myztro, he rose to fame after the release of "Emcimbini", "Dipatje tsa Felo" and "66", the latter certified Multi-Platinum by the Recording Industry of South Africa (RiSA). Myztro was born and raised in Soshanguve, he is the biological brother of South African DJ and record producer DJ Maphorisa. == Awards and nominations == Year Award ceremony Category Recipient/Nominated work Results 2021 Mzansi Kwaito and House Music Awards Most Voted Song "Emcimbini" 2022 All Africa Music Awards Best Artiste/Duo/Group in African Electro "66 & Dipatje Tsa Felo" 2023 Metro FM Music Awards Best Viral Challenge "Tobetsa" 2023 South African Music Awards Newcomer of the Year Nkwari 2.0 Best Amapiano Album Remix of the Year "Tobetsa Remake" == References == == Other websites == * Category:Date of birth missing (living people) Category:Living people Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:South African artists
